@author: janro

First_package_Rosa.add_func.approx_markov(rho, sigma_u, m=3, n=7)[source]¶

Computes the Markov matrix associated with a discretized version of the linear Gaussian AR(1) process

y_{t+1} = rho * y_t + u_{t+1}

according to Tauchen’s method. Here {u_t} is an iid Gaussian process with zero mean.

rho : scalar(float)
The autocorrelation coefficient
sigma_u : scalar(float)
The standard deviation of the random process
m : scalar(int), optional(default=3)
The number of standard deviations to approximate out to
n : scalar(int), optional(default=7)
The number of states to use in the approximation
x : array_like(float, ndim=1)
The state space of the discretized process
P : array_like(float, ndim=2)
The Markov transition matrix where P[i, j] is the probability of transitioning from x[i] to x[j]

First_package_Rosa.model_with_labour module¶

Created on Sat Jun 22 18:14:24 2019

@author: janro

class First_package_Rosa.model_with_labour.life_cycle_2(T=79, R=45, alpha=0.4, beta=0.98, r=0.02, sigma=2.0, rho_edu=0.98, sigma_AR_edu=0.018, rho_unedu=0.98, sigma_AR_unedu=0.0346, a_n=60, a_r=5, n_sim=3000, n_sim_ag=1, grid_min=0.0001, grid_max=100.0, edu_premium=[1.0, 1.34], edu_prop=[0.7, 0.3], ind_fe=[0.1517, 0.2061], n_fe=2, age_eff_coef_1=0.0, age_eff_coef_2=0.0, age_eff_coef_3=0.0, n_ag=5, mu_ag=1.0, sigma_ag=0.001, lambda_pref=5, chi=1.67)[source]¶

The life cycle model is here constructed.

Consumers life T periods, retire after R. Consumer may be educated or unecudated (i=0 or 1 for eductaed). Her productivity process is givan as: log p_{j,t,i} &= kappa_i + eta_{j,t,i} + gamma_1 j -gamma_2 j^{2} -gamma_1 j^3 eta_{j+1,t+1} &=

ho_i eta_{j,t} + epsilon_{j,t,i}

kappa_i &sim N(0, sigma_i)

Where kappa_i are fixed effects, eta_{j,t,i} is AR productivity process. Prarmetrs to calibrate a model are from Kindermann & Kruger (2017) and Kopecky (2017)

She optimize savings (a_{j,t}) and consumption (c_{j,t}) during the life time, write to bugdet constraint given by wage w_t and productivity p_{j,t,i} thus solve a problem:

max_{a_{j+1,t+1},c_{j,t}} u(c_{j,t})+Esum_{k=0}pi_{j+i,t+i} eta^k u(c_{j+k,t+k}) c_{j,t} +a_{j+1,t+1} <= ed_i w_t p_{j,t,i} ilde{P}_t + (1 +r_t)a_{j,t} where:

ilde{P}_t - aggregate shock

pi_{j+i,t+i} - probabilty of surviving to period t+i ed_i - education premium
